						<summary>

						<p>On the sixth face of the fourth pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 30: 936-37 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records the gift of 90 sheep for a perpetual lamp to the god Mādēva at Tirumaṟaikkāḍu by Āṭṭi Śaḍaiyan, the headman of Kiḷiyūr.</p>						

